The Analysis in R
Here’s the core optimization logic (simplified):
# Allocate pharmacies across counties
allocate_pharmacies &lt;- function(df, n) {
  df |&gt;
    mutate(
      pharmacies = 1,  # Each county gets 1 base
      pop_ratio = pop / sum(pop)
    ) |&gt;
    # Distribute remaining proportionally
    mutate(extra_pharmacies = floor(pop_ratio * (n - nrow(df)))) |&gt;
    mutate(total_pharmacies = pharmacies + extra_pharmacies)
}

# Find optimal locations using MCLP
find_optimal_locations &lt;- function(county, radius, n_pharmacies) {
  maxcovr::max_coverage(
    proposed_facility = pharmacies_in_county,
    user = populated_areas,
    n_added = n_pharmacies,
    distance_cutoff = radius  # 10km
  )
}
I ran this analysis for scenarios ranging from 50 to 700 pharmacies, calculating coverage metrics for each. This systematic approach allowed me to identify the point of diminishing returns.
